      "body": "Hi Wladimir,\n\nI respectfully disagree with your assertion. A HW error would be evident\nregardless of the OS, application SW or system utility. I can search the\nHDD file system with my OSX browser, verify it with Discutil and mount it\non a Linux and Windows OS OK.\n\nThis is the 3rd failure now on three separate devices, a 65gb high speed\nSD card, a 128gb USB2 HDD, a 128gb USB3 HDD.\n\nI wanted to know how to reindex and create a new checksum, is it possible?\n\nRegards,\n\nG*\n\nOn Tuesday, 9 February 2016, Wladimir J. van der Laan <\nnotifications@github.com> wrote:\n\n> This is a duplicate of #7426\n> https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/7426. Mostly these corruption\n> issues are caused by faulty hardware.\n> \n> —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/7479#issuecomment-181853188.\n",
